    "description": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">At 6th level, whenever you cast a spell of 1st level or higher that restores hit points you gain a death die.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">Whenever you cast a spell of 1st level or higher that deals damage, you gain a life die.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">Both of these dice start as d4s, and if you cast the appropriate type of spell while you already have one its size increases by one step, to a maximum of a d12.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">When you cast a spell of 1st level or higher that restores hit points you can spend your life die to roll it and add it to one healing roll for the spell.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">When you cast a spell of 1st level or higher that deals damage you can spend your death die to roll it and add it to one damage roll for the spell.</p>",
